# Spectral Learning — PCA & SVD from Scratch

Dimensionality reduction on the Wine Quality dataset using Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and Singular Value Decomposition (SVD), both implemented from scratch using NumPy.

---

## Objectives

- Implement PCA and SVD without scikit-learn's decomposition classes
- Understand the mechanics of eigenvalue decomposition and matrix factorization
- Evaluate reduced representations using clustering and variance metrics
- Visualize data structure in 2D/3D reduced space

---

## Project Structure

```
spectral-learning/
├── data/
│   ├── winequality-red.csv
│   └── winequality-white.csv
├── models/
│   ├── pca_model.py       # PCA from scratch (eig decomposition)
│   ├── svd_model.py       # SVD from scratch (numpy.linalg.svd)
│   └── __init__.py
├── utils/
│   ├── data_loader.py     # Load + standardize Wine Quality data
│   ├── matrix_operations.py  # Shared: center_matrix, covariance_matrix, reconstruct
│   ├── clustering.py      # K-Means + silhouette scoring + optimal k sweep
│   ├── visualization.py   # All plots: variance, 2D/3D, clusters, loadings
│   └── __init__.py
├── main.py                # Full pipeline
├── README.md
└── requirements.txt
```

